kind decision
title Stale detection via edges, not git log
edge applies-to blob:a4f8876768c98d00f302d7bddf6b72a01f5027fc
edge targets-path path:mycelium.sh

The three planning sessions designed applies-to + targets-path as a pair
specifically so staleness could be detected without walking git history.
If a note has targets-path path:X but applies-to blob:Y, and the current
blob at X is Z != Y, the note is stale. Simple comparison, no git log.
This is what Session 2 called 'drifted' and Session 1 called 'contextual.'

Also: removed the [edge] scan from context — it was a superset of the
stale scan and produced duplicates. Stale + inherited + commit is sufficient.
